🏠💡 Home Automation Using NodeMCU & Blynk

📌 Problem Statement:
Manual control of home appliances is inconvenient and lacks remote access
functionality. Forgetting to turn off devices wastes energy and money! 💸🔌

🎯 Objective:
Create a smart home automation system using NodeMCU and Blynk to
control appliances like lights 💡, fans 🌀, and more — all from your smartphone,
anywhere in the world! 🌍📱

🛠️ Hardware & Software Requirements:
• 📶 NodeMCU ESP8266 (Wi-Fi microcontroller)
• ⚡ 2-Channel or 4-Channel Relay Module
• 💡 LED bulbs / LEDs (for demonstration)
• 📱 Blynk App (Android/iOS) for remote control
• 🔌 Jumper wires, breadboard
• 🔋 Power supply

🔬 How It Works:
1️⃣ NodeMCU connects to your home Wi-Fi network 📶
2️⃣ Blynk app sends ON/OFF commands to the NodeMCU 📲
3️⃣ NodeMCU triggers the relay module to switch appliances ⚡
4️⃣ Control lights, fans, and devices from anywhere! 🌐✨

🏆 Expected Outcome:
A fully functional remote-controlled smart home system that switches
appliances ON/OFF via smartphone 📱 — making your home smarter,
more energy-efficient ♻️, and incredibly convenient! 🏡✨

